# Sūra XLIII.: Zu<u>kh</u>ruf, or Gold Adornments.

### Section 3

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_026.gif)

26. Wa-i<u>th</u> q<u>a</u>la ibr<u>a</u>heemu li-abeehi waqawmihi
innanee bar<u>a</u>on mimm<u>a</u> taAAbudoon**a**

26\. Behold! Abraham said  
To his father and his people:  
"I do indeed clear myself  
Of what ye worship:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_027.gif)

27. Ill<u>a</u> alla<u>th</u>ee fa<u>t</u>aranee fa-innahu
sayahdeen**i**

27\. "(I worship) only Him  
Who made me, and He  
Will certainly guide me."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_028.gif)

28. WajaAAalah<u>a</u> kalimatan b<u>a</u>qiyatan fee AAaqibihi
laAAallahum yarjiAAoon**a**

28\. And he left it  
As a Word  
To endure among those  
Who came after him,  
That they may turn back  
(To God).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_029.gif)

29. Bal mattaAAtu h<u>a</u>ol<u>a</u>-i wa<u>a</u>b<u>a</u>ahum
<u>h</u>att<u>a</u> j<u>a</u>ahumu al<u>h</u>aqqu warasoolun
mubeen**un**

29\. Yea, I have given  
The good things of this life  
To these (men) and  
Their fathers, until the Truth  
Has come to them,  
And an Apostle  
Making things clear.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_030.gif)

30. Walamm<u>a</u> j<u>a</u>ahumu al<u>h</u>aqqu q<u>a</u>loo
h<u>atha</u> si<u>h</u>run wa-inn<u>a</u> bihi k<u>a</u>firoon**a**

30\. But when the Truth came  
To them, they said:  
"This is sorcery, and we  
Do reject it."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_031.gif)

31. Waq<u>a</u>loo lawl<u>a</u> nuzzila h<u>atha</u> alqur-<u>a</u>nu
AAal<u>a</u> rajulin mina alqaryatayni AAa*<u>th</u>*eem**un**

31\. Also, they say: "Why  
Is not this Qur-ān sent  
Down to some leading man  
In either of the two  
(Chief) cities?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_032.gif)

32. Ahum yaqsimoona ra<u>h</u>mata rabbika na<u>h</u>nu qasamn<u>a</u>
baynahum maAAeeshatahum fee al<u>h</u>ay<u>a</u>ti a**l**dduny<u>a</u>
warafaAAn<u>a</u> baAA<u>d</u>ahum fawqa baAA<u>d</u>in daraj<u>a</u>tin
liyattakhi<u>th</u>a baAA<u>d</u>uhum baAA<u>d</u>an sukhriyyan
wara<u>h</u>matu rabbika khayrun mimm<u>a</u> yajmaAAoon**a**

32\. Is it they who would portion out  
The Mercy of thy Lord?  
It is We Who portion out  
Between them their livelihood  
In the life of this world:  
And We raise some of them  
Above others in ranks,  
So that some may command  
Work from others.  
But the Mercy of thy Lord  
Is better than the (wealth)  
Which they amass.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_033.gif)

33. Walawl<u>a</u> an yakoona a**l**nn<u>a</u>su ommatan
w<u>ah</u>idatan lajaAAaln<u>a</u> liman yakfuru
bi**al**rra<u>h</u>m<u>a</u>ni libuyootihim suqufan min fi<u>dd</u>atin
wamaAA<u>a</u>rija AAalayh<u>a</u> ya*<u>th</u>*haroon**a**

33\. And were it not that  
(All) men might become  
Of one (evil) way of life,  
We would provide,  
For everyone that blasphemes  
Against (God) Most Gracious,  
Silver roofs for their houses,  
And (silver) stair-ways  
On which to go up,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_034.gif)

34. Walibuyootihim abw<u>a</u>ban wasururan AAalayh<u>a</u>
yattaki-oon**a**

34\. And (silver) doors  
To their houses, and thrones  
(Of silver) on which  
They could recline,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/043/043_035.gif)

35. Wazukhrufan wa-in kullu <u>tha</u>lika lamm<u>a</u> mat<u>a</u>AAu
al<u>h</u>ay<u>a</u>ti a**l**dduny<u>a</u> wa**a**l-<u>a</u>khiratu
AAinda rabbika lilmuttaqeen**a**

35\. And also adornments  
Of gold. But all this  
Were nothing but conveniences  
Of the present life:  
The Hereafter, in the sight  
Of thy Lord, is  
For the Righteous.

